'''Agora Energiewende''' is a [[think tank]] supporting the [[Energiewende in Germany|''Energiewende'']] in [[Germany]].  It is funded by {{Interlanguage link multi|Stiftung Mercator|de}} and the [[European Climate Foundation]].<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.cleanenergywire.org/experts/agora-energiewende |website= cleanenergywire.org |title= Agora Energiewende |year= 2017 |accessdate= 2017-03-09}}</ref>

Its members debate under the [[Chatham House Rule]] and include [[Klaus Töpfer]], [[Ottmar Edenhofer]], and [[Claude Turmes]].

In addition to studies specific to Germany, Agora have published an analysis on the economics of the proposed [[United Kingdom|UK]] [[Hinkley Point C]] nuclear power plant.<ref>{{cite web| first= Daniel |last= Fürstenwerth |title = Comparing the cost of low-carbon technologies : what is the cheapest option? : an analysis of new wind, solar, nuclear and CCS based on current support schemes in the UK and Germany|year = 2014|website= agora-energiewende.de |place = [[Berlin]], Germany|url = http://www.agora-energiewende.de/fileadmin/Projekte/2014/low-carbon-technologies/Agora_Analysis_Decarbonisationtechnologies_web_final.pdf| format= [[PDF]] |access-date = 2017-03-09}}</ref>  Its analyses are quoted as part of the energy debate in other countries, including Denmark.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://politiken.dk/oekonomi/2050/groen_omstilling/art5594211/Tyskerne-installerer-sol-som-aldrig-f%C3%B8r-%C2%BBKonen-var-ikke-s%C3%A5-vild-med-det%C2%AB |title= Tyskerne installerer sol som aldrig før: »Konen var ikke så vild med det« |work= [[Politiken]] |first= Thomas |last= Færgeman |date= 2015-10-19 |accessdate= 2017-03-09 |language= da |trans-title=The Germans install solar like never before: »The wife was not that wild about it«}}</ref>

