'''Amazon Wind Farm Texas''' is a 253 Megawatt [[wind farm]] in [[Scurry County]], [[West Texas]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dallasnews.com/business/retail/2017/09/07/amazoncoms-jeff-bezos-big-roots-intexas-give-state-edge|title=Jeff Bezos' roots could give Texas an edge as Amazon.com looks for new HQ site|publisher=The Dallas Morning News|date=2017-09-07|last=Halkias|first=Maria|access-date=2017-09-27}}</ref>  The farm opened in late 2017,<ref>[[https://www.cnbc.com/2017/10/19/amazons-jeff-bezos-has-just-opened-a-massive-wind-farm-in-texas.html Amazon's Jeff Bezos just opened a massive wind farm in Texas]] 
Anmar Frangoul CNBC Published 10:57 AM ET Thu, 19 Oct 2017 Updated 2:41 PM ET Thu, 19 Oct 2017</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Associated Press |url=http://kxan.com/2016/09/16/amazon-announces-plan-for-west-texas-wind-farm/ |title=Amazon announces plan for West Texas wind farm |publisher=KXAN.com |date= |accessdate=2016-09-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/p/feature/ps9c2vfu7fcm4t6?ref_=aa_lc_0&pf_rd_r=6F894AHA5W2FQZBQTYZB&pf_rd_p=3fffa90a-17f6-470a-82ad-414308e970a2 |title=About Amazon Blog - Our Largest Wind Farm Yet |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=2016-09-18}}</ref> the project includes over 100 [[Wind turbine | turbines]] which generate and feed into the Texas electric grid 1,000,000 megawatt hours of [[Wind power | wind energy]] annually (1,000 gigawatt hours), enough to power 90,000 typical US homes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news-journal.com/news/2016/sep/16/amazon-invests-in-texas-wind-farm/ |title=Amazon invests in Texas wind farm - Longview News-Journal - Longview, TX |publisher=News-journal.com |date= |accessdate=2016-09-18}}</ref>

October 19, 2017, Amazon's Jeff Bezos christened the Amazon Wind Farm Texas by smashing a champagne bottle on top of one of the turbines standing more than {{convert|300|feet|m}} tall. In a statement, Amazon revealed that it has entered into an agreement to purchase 90 percent of the facility's output. The facility was built by Lincoln Clean Energy which also owns and operates the wind farm. This facility is one example of Amazon's large and increasing long-term investment in [[renewable energy]].  

